headline.main: THE PACIFIC COAST.; Intelligence from the Isthmus and South America. Later From Oregon and Washington. Interesting from the Sandwich Islands. DETAILS OF CALIFORNIA NEWS. ARRIVAL OF THE MOSES TAYLOR. $1,643,204 in Treasure.

docs.lead_paragraph: The United States man steamship moses Taylor, A. G. GRAY, Esp., commanding, from Aspinwall Dec. 4, with the passengers, mails, and treasure, brought from San Francisco by the Golden Age, Nov. 20, arrived at this port yesterday. The Moses Taylor left the United States steam-frigate Roanoke in the harbor of Aspinwall. All hands well.

docs.lead_paragraph: SECOND LECTURE OF THE HON. CALEB LYON. The second lecture of the Hon. CALEB LYON an the Holy Land, was delivered under the auspices of the Mercantile Library Association at Clinton Hall last evening. The audience quite filled the hall. The lecture,-which was much of it of a descriptive character,-was much more interesting thao it can be made to appear in a report of limited length, and its delivery was earnest and effective.
